# Source Code Examples

This folder contains representative C++ source code examples from the Modular Interaction Framework developed in Unreal Engine 5.

These files are provided to demonstrate coding style, class structure, and C++/Blueprint integration patterns used in the system.

> **Note:** Some source files and implementation details are not included due to proprietary restrictions related to the original commercial VR training project. As a result, some classes in this folder may appear incomplete or may reference systems that are not included in this repository.

The full system architecture and design are documented in:
**Docs/Architecture_Explanation.md**

Additional documentation for specific components can be found in the **Docs/** folder.
